{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"02e5f3fb-0e87-4943-8b0a-aacd8c8901c8","content":"Two things change with xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n### 1. Filter syntax changes\n\nThe VSTest `--filter` syntax (`FullyQualifiedName~X&Category=Y`) is replaced by MTP's `--filter` syntax. The equivalent is:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests and Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nKey differences:\n- **`&`** → **`and`** (logical operators are words: `and`, `or`, `not`)\n- `~` (contains), `=` (equals), `!=` (not equals) still work the same\n- You can also use the MTP-native executable directly: `./TestProject --filter \"...\"`\n\n### 2. `[Trait]` attribute → `[Category]` shorthand (optional)\n\nxUnit v3 still supports `[Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]`, but also adds a first-class `[Category]` attribute you may prefer:\n\n```csharp\n[Category(\"Smoke\")]  // equivalent to [Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]\n```\n\n### Your CI command\n\n```diff\n- dotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n+ dotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests and Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nThat's all — the `&` → `and` replacement is the critical fix.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"13664573-2b4f-4985-9faf-715630c620a1","outputTokens":343},"id":"01ee31dc-f330-4f86-a2b0-060abd4123cd","timestamp":"2026-04-07T15:55:57.703Z","parentId":"c40ebf8d-6f50-469c-b82f-4bfb7501a0fa"}
